        "subject": "LU-5526 ldlm: fix bug in LDLM_FL_AST_MASK",
        "message": "LU-5526 ldlm: fix bug in LDLM_FL_AST_MASK\n\nwhen the blocking ast is sent to the clients, the server set\nLDLM_FL_DISCARD_DATA in ldlm_request->lock_flags instead of\nLDLM_FL_AST_DISCARD_DATA, which is contained in LDLM_FL_AST_MASK\nincorrectly and the dirty pages at clients can't be discarded.\n\nTest-Parameters: alwaysuploadlogs \\\nenvdefinitions=SLOW=yes,ENABLE_QUOTA=yes,REQFAIL=100,DURATION=28800 \\\nmdtfilesystemtype=zfs mdsfilesystemtype=zfs ostfilesystemtype=zfs \\\nclientdistro=el6 ossdistro=el6 mdsdistro=el6 clientarch=x86_64 \\\nossarch=x86_64 mdsarch=x86_64 clientcount=4 osscount=2 mdscount=2 \\\nmdssizegb=10 ostsizegb=10 austeroptions=-R failover=true iscsi=1 \\\ntestlist=recovery-mds-scale\n\nChange-Id: I6723a35e26622c0cda703e0175e647c0eb7b87bb\nSigned-off-by: Hongchao Zhang <hongchao.zhang@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
